WEBVTT

00:00:10.281 --> 00:00:12.992
Why are you not dating anyone?

00:00:13.493 --> 00:00:14.786
I'm more comfortable alone.

00:00:14.869 --> 00:00:17.789
What inconvenienced you
when you were with someone else?

00:00:17.872 --> 00:00:19.124
Not having time for myself.

00:00:19.207 --> 00:00:21.626
-What physical characteristics…
-Thick eyebrows.

00:00:23.878 --> 00:00:26.548
Initiating personalized AI generation.

00:00:29.384 --> 00:00:31.386
Optimization complete.

00:01:24.564 --> 00:01:29.152
Congratulations on meeting Gu Yeong-il,
your custom-tailored boyfriend.

00:01:29.235 --> 00:01:30.069
Holy crap!

00:01:31.946 --> 00:01:33.615
Manager!

00:01:34.991 --> 00:01:36.284
SUBSCRIBERS: 1
A MAN JUST FOR ME

00:01:36.367 --> 00:01:38.036
I checked. There's nothing wrong.

00:01:38.119 --> 00:01:39.078
What?

00:01:39.704 --> 00:01:40.788
Excuse me.

00:01:43.166 --> 00:01:46.252
I was a bit overwhelmed,
so I may not have explained it clearly.

00:01:46.336 --> 00:01:50.173
But there's a serious defect
with his face, okay?

00:01:50.256 --> 00:01:52.467
No, he looked handsome to me.

00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:54.636
Whatever. Just make it again.

00:01:56.012 --> 00:01:57.347
-Again?
-Yes.

00:01:57.430 --> 00:02:01.267
I didn't go through over 2,000 questions
just to see that face, you know.

00:02:01.351 --> 00:02:02.936
That man…

00:02:03.519 --> 00:02:04.938
I mean, Gu Yeong-il…

00:02:07.357 --> 00:02:08.274
Anyway, no.

00:02:08.358 --> 00:02:11.194
He's been custom-tailored just for you.

00:02:11.277 --> 00:02:14.530
We threw in everything you like.

00:02:15.031 --> 00:02:17.116
Keep going.
I'm sure you'll change your mind.

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:19.077
We have to make another one.

00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:19.994
Absolutely not.

00:02:20.870 --> 00:02:24.540
I told you, didn't I?
You can only make number 901 once.

00:02:25.208 --> 00:02:28.711
But this is a different case. His face--

00:02:28.795 --> 00:02:31.130
What's all this about his face?

00:02:31.214 --> 00:02:33.758
Is he a cyclops?
Does he have three nostrils?

00:02:33.841 --> 00:02:36.511
It's not our fault.
That's just how your ideal man looks.

00:02:36.594 --> 00:02:37.637
What?

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:40.265
No. He's not my ideal man.

00:02:40.348 --> 00:02:41.349
That's not possible.

00:02:42.558 --> 00:02:45.645
I took those questions seriously
and answered them sincerely.

00:02:45.728 --> 00:02:48.022
We also took this very seriously.

00:02:48.106 --> 00:02:49.399
Rules are rules.

00:02:49.482 --> 00:02:50.608
No do-overs.

00:02:55.655 --> 00:02:59.117
Are they out of their damn minds?
They must be crazy!

00:03:07.875 --> 00:03:10.461
Consultations are not available
at this hour.

00:03:11.212 --> 00:03:12.714
Damn it!

00:03:12.797 --> 00:03:15.049
I mean, of all people,

00:03:16.134 --> 00:03:17.635
why did it have to be…

00:03:19.012 --> 00:03:20.013
That won't work.

00:03:20.096 --> 00:03:21.097
I like you.

00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:24.183
-I am seeing someone right now.
-All right.

00:03:25.893 --> 00:03:27.770
Why did it have to be his face?

00:03:27.854 --> 00:03:30.898
EPISODE 6
THE HYBRID MAN

00:03:45.413 --> 00:03:46.247
Hello.

00:03:47.665 --> 00:03:48.499
Hi.

00:03:51.919 --> 00:03:53.504
Doors closing.

00:04:17.528 --> 00:04:19.155
Doors opening.

00:04:23.701 --> 00:04:24.786
Aren't you getting off?

00:04:33.086 --> 00:04:35.713
You seem to value originality,
Producer Park,

00:04:36.297 --> 00:04:38.257
but this piece just doesn't hit me.

00:04:39.217 --> 00:04:42.387
It's unrefined,
but it has a clear theme and good artwork.

00:04:45.598 --> 00:04:47.600
Whoever drew this
is probably an art major.

00:04:48.309 --> 00:04:52.397
If we could refine the panel composition,
it'd be much better than it is now.

00:04:52.480 --> 00:04:55.650
I think you're suggesting
that we should look at the potential…

00:04:55.733 --> 00:04:58.736
Park Kyeong-nam is identical
to my ideal man?

00:04:58.820 --> 00:05:01.823
That's the purpose of our contest.
It's also good in the long run.

00:05:01.906 --> 00:05:03.908
There is just no way.

00:05:03.991 --> 00:05:06.744
An author with clear pros and cons
is easier to work with…

00:05:06.828 --> 00:05:08.037
But wait.

00:05:08.746 --> 00:05:10.748
I didn't know he had inner double eyelids.

00:05:12.166 --> 00:05:13.543
That's how I like them.

00:05:14.502 --> 00:05:17.422
He's also got a straight nose.

00:05:17.964 --> 00:05:20.133
And those lips…

00:05:31.978 --> 00:05:33.896
Just stop it, you crazy girl.

00:05:38.067 --> 00:05:39.318
Do you not agree?

00:05:39.402 --> 00:05:40.319
Huh?

00:05:41.988 --> 00:05:43.698
I do agree.

00:05:45.074 --> 00:05:46.284
This is good.

00:05:58.129 --> 00:05:59.464
What is up with you today?

00:06:02.008 --> 00:06:03.009
What do you mean?

00:06:03.092 --> 00:06:05.219
You jump every time
I catch you looking at me.

00:06:05.303 --> 00:06:08.556
Well, that's not…

00:06:09.056 --> 00:06:11.476
Your face was just, you know…

00:06:11.559 --> 00:06:12.602
What about my face?

00:06:13.186 --> 00:06:14.854
Your face is a bit…

00:06:18.232 --> 00:06:19.317
Is it a common face?

00:06:19.901 --> 00:06:20.735
What?

00:06:20.818 --> 00:06:25.531
I mean, it's not one of those faces
you can see just anywhere, is it?

00:06:26.949 --> 00:06:28.034
I don't understand--

00:06:28.117 --> 00:06:29.994
Food is here!

00:06:30.536 --> 00:06:31.829
Food is here!

00:06:32.371 --> 00:06:33.539
Let's eat first.

00:06:46.552 --> 00:06:49.889
Nope. No way in hell.

00:06:55.102 --> 00:06:56.270
Aren't you going to eat?

00:06:57.980 --> 00:06:58.981
Thank you.

00:07:06.739 --> 00:07:08.241
Not a chance.

00:07:12.912 --> 00:07:14.163
That one's mine.

00:07:19.001 --> 00:07:21.212
Well, sorry about that.

00:07:27.176 --> 00:07:29.554
Is the world pranking me right now?

00:07:33.641 --> 00:07:34.642
Damn it!

00:07:48.239 --> 00:07:49.615
I'm getting this one too.

00:07:51.492 --> 00:07:54.161
Just stop.
How are you even splurging at a bookstore?

00:07:54.245 --> 00:07:56.664
I can't buy clothes now.
Might as well get some books.

00:07:56.747 --> 00:07:58.541
I bought stuff for my blind date,

00:07:58.624 --> 00:08:01.127
and my credit card bills
are gonna get me evicted.

00:08:01.210 --> 00:08:02.878
A blind date? So soon?

00:08:03.462 --> 00:08:05.631
"So soon"? I've been single for ages.

00:08:05.715 --> 00:08:06.799
Has it been two weeks?

00:08:08.092 --> 00:08:10.636
Exactly. I should get back out there.

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:12.597
I've got two dates tomorrow.

00:08:13.347 --> 00:08:15.141
Oh, this is great.

00:08:15.224 --> 00:08:18.769
Why don't you look for a guy
to set me up with?

00:08:18.853 --> 00:08:20.730
You just said you have two dates tomorrow.

00:08:20.813 --> 00:08:24.525
Hey, don't you know people read
multiple books at the same time now?

00:08:24.609 --> 00:08:27.069
No one goes around
seeing just one guy at a time.

00:08:29.196 --> 00:08:31.032
Kim…

00:08:31.115 --> 00:08:32.199
Kim Yeong-hun.

00:08:32.283 --> 00:08:34.785
He has a girlfriend? Since when?

00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:38.414
Anyone from Naemo?

00:08:39.165 --> 00:08:40.082
Park Kyeong…

00:08:40.166 --> 00:08:41.917
Huh? You're already at Park?

00:08:42.001 --> 00:08:46.380
Seo Hyeon-uk also has a girlfriend, and…

00:08:46.464 --> 00:08:47.632
Jeong-sik.

00:08:47.715 --> 00:08:48.799
He has a child?

00:08:48.883 --> 00:08:50.176
I think she goes to school.

00:08:50.259 --> 00:08:51.260
Cute.

00:08:53.387 --> 00:08:54.764
What? Is that it?

00:08:55.723 --> 00:08:56.974
There isn't a single guy?

00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:00.019
Just what I thought.

00:09:00.102 --> 00:09:00.936
Hey.

00:09:01.646 --> 00:09:03.189
When did everyone get snapped up?

00:09:04.231 --> 00:09:06.901
Why so surprised?
You're not even interested in dating.

00:09:08.027 --> 00:09:10.196
Things have been this bad for a while now.

00:09:13.032 --> 00:09:15.242
Does that mean
all the decent men are taken,

00:09:16.952 --> 00:09:18.996
even if I wanted to date one?

00:09:26.671 --> 00:09:28.589
Things will be different this holiday.

00:09:34.762 --> 00:09:36.389
Because you'll have…

00:09:41.435 --> 00:09:44.021
Boyfriend on Demand next to you.

00:09:59.036 --> 00:10:01.455
Fine. I'll fall for it.

00:10:02.206 --> 00:10:03.541
Just this once.

00:10:32.236 --> 00:10:33.487
Your engine's totally shot.

00:10:34.864 --> 00:10:35.865
Excuse me?

00:10:35.948 --> 00:10:38.868
I saw the smoke and followed you.
Where are you headed?

00:10:39.577 --> 00:10:40.995
Oh, I…

00:10:42.830 --> 00:10:44.123
I don't know.

00:10:44.707 --> 00:10:47.084
I was just driving along this road.

00:10:48.627 --> 00:10:49.462
Are you a tourist?

00:10:51.255 --> 00:10:52.089
A tourist?

00:11:08.147 --> 00:11:09.690
Follow me if you want.

00:11:10.983 --> 00:11:14.570
"What's the most romantic first encounter
you've ever dreamed of?"

00:11:14.653 --> 00:11:18.157
Going on a trip
and meeting a guy with a free spirit

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:21.076
at an unfamiliar place,
just like in a movie.

00:11:22.495 --> 00:11:24.246
It's dangerous here at night.

00:11:26.707 --> 00:11:29.502
-You want me to get on that?
-Then are you going to stay here?

00:11:30.628 --> 00:11:32.880
No, thanks. I'm scared.

00:11:47.394 --> 00:11:49.980
Before I even realized it, I got on.

00:12:05.579 --> 00:12:06.580
This feels weird.

00:12:07.456 --> 00:12:11.961
I'm riding behind a stranger
who looks just like Park Kyeong-nam,

00:12:12.545 --> 00:12:15.464
and I don't even know
where we're going, so why…

00:12:17.633 --> 00:12:20.970
Why is his back so comfy
that it feels like it was made for me?

00:12:32.022 --> 00:12:33.691
And the wind, it's so…

00:12:40.739 --> 00:12:42.575
It's so perfect.

00:12:45.369 --> 00:12:46.620
And his smell…

00:12:55.004 --> 00:12:55.963
How nice.

00:13:04.013 --> 00:13:05.347
What is this feeling?

00:13:21.196 --> 00:13:22.615
-Come on in.
-Yeong-il.

00:13:35.419 --> 00:13:36.420
Hi.

00:13:38.881 --> 00:13:42.051
Why is everything so detailed?
It feels so real.

00:13:53.896 --> 00:13:54.730
Oh my God.

00:13:55.356 --> 00:13:56.857
Bartender. Yeong-il's friend.

00:13:56.941 --> 00:13:59.443
People get scared when they first see me.
I don't bite though.

00:14:00.611 --> 00:14:01.987
I've seen you before.

00:14:03.072 --> 00:14:04.823
You really startled me!

00:14:06.784 --> 00:14:09.328
I'll have my usual, and for her--

00:14:09.411 --> 00:14:11.580
Hold up. Let me guess.

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.148
-No way.
-Is it to your liking?

00:14:39.316 --> 00:14:41.485
-Totally.
-Just holler when you're done.

00:14:44.321 --> 00:14:45.739
What brings you here all alone?

00:14:46.573 --> 00:14:49.493
You know,
I just needed to get my life in order.

00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:54.289
Actually,
I recently went through a breakup.

00:14:55.708 --> 00:14:56.542
May I ask why?

00:14:57.626 --> 00:14:58.585
He was a cheater.

00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:00.754
He met another woman?

00:15:02.006 --> 00:15:02.840
Try 10,000.

00:15:07.136 --> 00:15:08.137
Say what?

00:15:09.596 --> 00:15:10.848
Ten thousand women.

00:15:19.231 --> 00:15:23.527
This is the dining area.
You can have coffee in there anytime.

00:15:24.778 --> 00:15:25.779
Thank you.

00:15:26.864 --> 00:15:30.617
You can sleep in that room.
I'll give the owner a heads-up.

00:15:31.201 --> 00:15:32.077
Here.

00:15:35.956 --> 00:15:37.458
It was nice meeting you today.

00:15:54.808 --> 00:15:55.684
Su-ji?

00:15:56.185 --> 00:15:58.020
Hey, Su-ji!

00:15:58.103 --> 00:16:00.773
It's been so long! How have you been?

00:16:02.357 --> 00:16:03.692
Mind your manners.

00:16:05.903 --> 00:16:07.112
Do you know me?

00:16:07.196 --> 00:16:08.989
Yu-ra, a Korean tourist.

00:16:11.742 --> 00:16:12.993
I used to.

00:16:13.077 --> 00:16:15.537
Actually, no. I don't know you.

00:16:15.621 --> 00:16:18.749
Looks like another weirdo has joined us.

00:16:23.128 --> 00:16:25.380
Please don't close that door.

00:16:25.881 --> 00:16:28.425
That door is broken, okay?

00:16:28.926 --> 00:16:30.260
Once it closes,

00:16:31.637 --> 00:16:32.638
it won't open.

00:16:34.223 --> 00:16:35.724
Didn't know. Sorry, honey.

00:16:37.601 --> 00:16:39.061
I still don't like your tone.

00:16:39.561 --> 00:16:40.771
Hey, mister!

00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:43.357
Who the hell brought this woman here?

00:16:46.110 --> 00:16:48.237
I liked her best when she was Su-ji.

00:16:49.029 --> 00:16:50.781
She's even worse than Ms. Choi.

00:17:05.462 --> 00:17:07.464
I can't believe
he brought me to his hostel.

00:17:09.883 --> 00:17:10.717
Wait.

00:17:11.885 --> 00:17:14.555
He's not going to barge in here, is he?

00:17:18.308 --> 00:17:19.977
Aren't you coming to dinner?

00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:22.604
Coming!

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:33.448
Goddamn it!

00:17:34.324 --> 00:17:36.660
This stuff is tasteless.

00:17:38.620 --> 00:17:39.746
I'm done eating.

00:17:46.211 --> 00:17:47.212
A tough roommate, huh?

00:17:48.463 --> 00:17:49.548
Yeah.

00:17:50.424 --> 00:17:52.509
Your car will be here
the morning after next.

00:17:53.177 --> 00:17:54.553
All right. Thanks.

00:17:57.598 --> 00:18:00.767
By the way, what do you do for a living?

00:18:02.686 --> 00:18:03.520
I draw.

00:18:03.604 --> 00:18:04.605
What?

00:18:05.230 --> 00:18:06.064
You draw?

00:18:08.108 --> 00:18:09.276
So you're an artist?

00:18:10.527 --> 00:18:12.613
I just travel around and draw what I like.

00:18:13.697 --> 00:18:14.740
Mi-rae.

00:18:14.823 --> 00:18:17.159
It's your turn now.
What's your dream guy like?

00:18:17.242 --> 00:18:18.410
My dream guy?

00:18:18.493 --> 00:18:20.412
Gang Dong-won for me. Ju Ji-hoon for her.

00:18:24.291 --> 00:18:25.125
For me,

00:18:26.001 --> 00:18:27.336
it's a hybrid man.

00:18:28.587 --> 00:18:30.714
-What's that?
-Look.

00:18:31.715 --> 00:18:35.219
Someone calm and pure at heart,

00:18:35.302 --> 00:18:37.638
with a genuine love for art.

00:18:45.312 --> 00:18:48.232
I've been playing ball.
You're studying during break time?

00:18:48.315 --> 00:18:50.734
But at the same time,
I want him to be wild and free.

00:18:51.985 --> 00:18:53.487
What is she talking about?

00:18:53.570 --> 00:18:55.197
What I'm saying is…

00:18:55.280 --> 00:18:58.867
It's like when you mix a little red
into white to get this subtle…

00:18:59.368 --> 00:19:02.579
-You get me, don't you?
-No. What is he, Santa Claus?

00:19:03.664 --> 00:19:04.790
Anyway…

00:19:07.334 --> 00:19:08.919
that's my dream guy.

00:19:10.587 --> 00:19:11.421
Both…

00:19:13.799 --> 00:19:17.469
We threw in everything you like.

00:19:20.889 --> 00:19:22.140
They made it work?

00:19:31.817 --> 00:19:33.235
-Hello.
-Hi.

00:19:44.454 --> 00:19:46.957
The heart just cannot lie, you know.

00:19:47.916 --> 00:19:50.335
It's dead silent
if you don't like a person.

00:19:50.961 --> 00:19:53.880
-You know what I mean, right?
-What are you getting at?

00:19:53.964 --> 00:19:55.632
I want to act cool about it,

00:19:55.716 --> 00:19:58.927
but whenever I think about him,
my heart just goes…

00:20:00.178 --> 00:20:01.179
And then…

00:20:02.180 --> 00:20:03.265
You know?

00:20:03.348 --> 00:20:06.393
Man, she's got it bad.
What kind of guy did you set her up with?

00:20:06.476 --> 00:20:09.938
He does have a way of sucking women in
like a swamp, but…

00:20:10.022 --> 00:20:12.357
If he hasn't contacted you in a week,
it's over.

00:20:12.441 --> 00:20:13.692
What is your problem?

00:20:13.775 --> 00:20:17.487
You should really try that thing.
To calm yourself down.

00:20:18.572 --> 00:20:20.490
-Nah, I'm good.
-Try what?

00:20:20.574 --> 00:20:22.242
-Boyfriend on Demand.
-Huh?

00:20:22.826 --> 00:20:24.995
Do people actually do Boyfriend on Demand?

00:20:26.371 --> 00:20:27.539
Really?

00:20:27.622 --> 00:20:30.625
-I thought it was all just marketing.
-So did I.

00:20:30.709 --> 00:20:34.046
I can hardly put money aside
with a tiny salary like mine.

00:20:34.129 --> 00:20:36.590
Who could afford to subscribe to that?

00:20:36.673 --> 00:20:38.633
A lot of my friends are subscribed to it.

00:20:38.717 --> 00:20:39.718
No way.

00:20:39.801 --> 00:20:40.802
No way!

00:20:40.886 --> 00:20:42.471
It's true. Think about it.

00:20:42.554 --> 00:20:46.725
Dating makes us spend so much money
and deal with an awful lot of stress.

00:20:46.808 --> 00:20:49.102
It saves you all that trouble.
How great is that?

00:20:49.186 --> 00:20:51.980
Besides, nowadays,
just by fangirling over idols,

00:20:52.064 --> 00:20:53.857
you spend that much every month.

00:20:54.358 --> 00:20:55.650
You do have a point.

00:20:56.568 --> 00:20:58.737
The world is doomed. It really is.

00:21:00.655 --> 00:21:02.032
That's a bit harsh.

00:21:02.115 --> 00:21:05.118
Now that I think about it,
was it 500,000 won?

00:21:06.495 --> 00:21:07.996
Right. 500,000.

00:21:08.080 --> 00:21:11.249
Okay. I do spend that much on eating out,

00:21:11.333 --> 00:21:15.003
watching movies,
going on trips and drives, and so on.

00:21:23.470 --> 00:21:26.473
As I thought, no reaction at all.

00:21:26.556 --> 00:21:28.892
Hey, you try contacting him.

00:21:30.769 --> 00:21:33.397
Go ahead, text him.
Does he ever talk about me?

00:21:34.481 --> 00:21:35.565
That's right.

00:21:35.649 --> 00:21:40.529
The guy I met yesterday and Kyeong-nam
are two completely different people.

00:21:54.918 --> 00:21:55.919
So different.

00:22:00.507 --> 00:22:01.591
Cheers.

00:22:07.556 --> 00:22:08.390
Aren't you bored?

00:22:09.850 --> 00:22:10.684
Nope.

00:22:11.476 --> 00:22:13.979
You've just been sitting here.
Anything caught your eye?

00:22:16.565 --> 00:22:17.566
You.

00:22:29.661 --> 00:22:32.581
This isn't a chair, you know.
Don't just sit on it.

00:22:35.959 --> 00:22:37.377
Are you having fun now?

00:22:37.461 --> 00:22:38.295
Yes.

00:22:39.045 --> 00:22:40.088
Let's go.

00:22:40.589 --> 00:22:41.590
There we go!

00:23:10.494 --> 00:23:11.661
Chaturanga.

00:23:12.704 --> 00:23:13.538
Head up.

00:23:20.337 --> 00:23:22.672
Lift your body and move into downward dog.

00:23:22.756 --> 00:23:23.757
Downward dog.

00:23:23.840 --> 00:23:25.926
Keep your heels on the floor.

00:23:26.009 --> 00:23:27.177
Okay.

00:23:27.260 --> 00:23:29.179
-Back to Chaturanga.
-Back to Chaturanga.

00:23:29.262 --> 00:23:31.014
Lift your head again,

00:23:31.097 --> 00:23:32.015
open your heart--

00:23:32.098 --> 00:23:34.434
Open my heart? Let me get a little closer.

00:23:34.518 --> 00:23:36.811
No, not like that. I meant exhale.

00:23:41.525 --> 00:23:42.526
How's that?

00:23:44.027 --> 00:23:44.861
Let go!

00:23:44.945 --> 00:23:47.030
Shut your mouth and breathe.

00:23:47.113 --> 00:23:49.032
-Stop!
-You need to breathe.

00:23:49.115 --> 00:23:51.535
-Let me go!
-Hamstring! Breathe!

00:23:57.082 --> 00:23:59.543
What's this? You've only drawn couples.

00:24:00.877 --> 00:24:02.796
I didn't feel like drawing other subjects.

00:24:04.506 --> 00:24:08.593
An artist who only draws couples.
How interesting.

00:24:10.011 --> 00:24:13.265
I don't draw just any couple I see.
I have standards.

00:24:16.309 --> 00:24:20.063
Those who don't doubt the future
and focus on the love in front of them.

00:24:20.647 --> 00:24:21.690
That's who I draw.

00:24:23.608 --> 00:24:24.442
Why is that?

00:24:25.235 --> 00:24:26.236
I don't know.

00:24:29.614 --> 00:24:31.783
Because it's sad when love changes.

00:24:34.786 --> 00:24:36.288
That must be why I record them.

00:24:44.671 --> 00:24:47.048
Let's go back.
The sun's going to set soon.

00:24:52.429 --> 00:24:53.471
What to do?

00:24:54.556 --> 00:24:55.390
Huh?

00:24:56.433 --> 00:24:59.519
I wasn't going to say anything,
but I'll be honest with you.

00:25:01.896 --> 00:25:02.731
About what?

00:25:02.814 --> 00:25:03.773
I think we're lost.

00:25:04.566 --> 00:25:05.400
What now?

00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:18.872
Stop messing with me.
I know you know the way.

00:25:19.623 --> 00:25:20.582
I'm serious.

00:25:21.082 --> 00:25:24.961
Yu-ra told me that a couple of newlyweds
went missing around here recently.

00:25:32.677 --> 00:25:34.596
What's your favorite movie genre?

00:25:35.930 --> 00:25:37.849
HORROR (OCCULT HORROR ESPECIALLY!)

00:25:37.932 --> 00:25:38.892
Those bastards.

00:25:39.392 --> 00:25:41.895
I said I liked to watch it,
not experience it!

00:25:42.395 --> 00:25:45.148
I don't like it here, okay? I hate it.

00:25:45.231 --> 00:25:46.232
Let's go…

00:26:02.499 --> 00:26:03.458
It's the owner's dog.

00:26:04.626 --> 00:26:05.710
Oh, I see.

00:26:07.837 --> 00:26:08.713
Are you that scared?

00:26:09.881 --> 00:26:12.217
No, well… just a little?

00:26:14.052 --> 00:26:15.345
I guess it is a bit dark.

00:26:40.578 --> 00:26:41.413
Not anymore.

00:27:04.436 --> 00:27:07.147
Keep going.
I'm sure you'll change your mind.

00:27:07.897 --> 00:27:09.315
Calm down.

00:27:09.858 --> 00:27:11.359
Calm down, for crying out loud!

00:27:13.862 --> 00:27:15.447
Doors closing.

00:27:25.206 --> 00:27:26.791
Doors opening.

00:27:27.959 --> 00:27:29.836
Excuse me. Coming through.

00:27:29.919 --> 00:27:31.796
Sorry. Excuse me.

00:27:32.839 --> 00:27:35.049
Sorry about that. I'm sorry.

00:27:35.133 --> 00:27:36.968
Doors closing.

00:27:48.021 --> 00:27:49.522
Seo Mi-rae, come to my office.

00:27:50.356 --> 00:27:52.942
Hey, Kyeong-nam, you too.

00:27:54.152 --> 00:27:55.987
Did you talk to Yun Song?

00:27:56.571 --> 00:27:58.823
Sorry? About what?

00:27:59.407 --> 00:28:01.534
Kyeong-nam said he told you.

00:28:02.619 --> 00:28:05.538
Hwany will be doing
the home appliance commercial.

00:28:06.956 --> 00:28:07.832
You didn't tell her?

00:28:08.792 --> 00:28:11.294
I'm sorry, sir. I'll tell her right away.

00:28:11.878 --> 00:28:13.963
Too late now! She would go berserk and…

00:28:14.047 --> 00:28:15.256
I can't even…

00:28:16.549 --> 00:28:20.386
That's that. You're supposed to attend
the BCF with Yun Song, aren't you?

00:28:20.470 --> 00:28:22.639
Take Kyeong-nam and Hwany with you.

00:28:23.848 --> 00:28:26.351
-What?
-I called you here to tell you that.

00:28:27.727 --> 00:28:29.813
Both of them were nominated this time.

00:28:30.772 --> 00:28:32.690
-Hwany too?
-That's right.

00:28:33.274 --> 00:28:36.486
And I get the feeling
at least one of them will win something.

00:28:36.569 --> 00:28:38.446
So take good care of your authors.

00:28:39.072 --> 00:28:40.031
Understand?

00:28:40.114 --> 00:28:40.949
Yes, sir.

00:28:41.574 --> 00:28:42.408
Yes, sir.

00:28:51.125 --> 00:28:52.335
So…

00:28:54.796 --> 00:28:57.549
Please tell Ms. Yun about it.
She won't take it well.

00:28:59.133 --> 00:29:01.302
Don't worry. I'll try to soften the blow.

00:29:01.970 --> 00:29:03.096
Ms. Seo.

00:29:04.013 --> 00:29:05.014
Yes?

00:29:07.976 --> 00:29:08.935
Why do you do that?

00:29:10.311 --> 00:29:12.063
What… do you mean?

00:29:12.981 --> 00:29:15.149
You're avoiding me
when I'm the one who got rejected.

00:29:18.403 --> 00:29:20.280
I never did that. When did I do that?

00:29:21.364 --> 00:29:23.366
I know you're uncomfortable around me,

00:29:24.742 --> 00:29:26.327
but could you try not to show it?

00:29:29.622 --> 00:29:31.165
This is upsetting for me as well.

00:29:47.640 --> 00:29:49.392
Hey, are you insane?

00:29:49.475 --> 00:29:50.852
Why did that go to him?

00:29:50.935 --> 00:29:53.730
Well, the advertiser requested it.

00:29:53.813 --> 00:29:57.525
They chose to deliver their ads
with his shitty drawings and not mine?

00:29:57.609 --> 00:29:58.860
Have they gone cuckoo?

00:29:58.943 --> 00:30:00.069
Ms. Yun,

00:30:00.153 --> 00:30:02.322
I'll make sure to find you a better ad--

00:30:04.324 --> 00:30:05.366
She hung up on me.

00:30:06.993 --> 00:30:08.995
God, this is so annoying!

00:30:15.793 --> 00:30:17.795
You all know
IG is the best brand there is.

00:30:18.296 --> 00:30:20.965
Coming soon,
PlanC and IG's collab webtoon.

00:30:21.049 --> 00:30:22.133
I'll do my best!

00:30:22.216 --> 00:30:24.218
Let's make PlanC number one!

00:30:24.302 --> 00:30:25.386
"Number one"?

00:30:26.054 --> 00:30:27.764
Why, that little prick…

00:30:36.272 --> 00:30:38.524
KOREAN BEEF INTESTINES

00:30:39.525 --> 00:30:40.526
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:30:44.781 --> 00:30:47.116
I'm so sick of greasy food
from all my blind dates.

00:30:49.619 --> 00:30:50.703
That's more like it.

00:30:50.787 --> 00:30:52.080
Did your dates go well?

00:30:53.122 --> 00:30:54.666
It was a disaster.

00:30:54.749 --> 00:30:56.834
Two dates in one day was a stretch.

00:30:56.918 --> 00:31:00.505
Their paths crossed, and somehow,
my dates ran into each other.

00:31:02.548 --> 00:31:04.634
I knew you were going to mess up.

00:31:04.717 --> 00:31:07.887
But the thing is, I went on another date
a few days after that.

00:31:10.056 --> 00:31:12.225
The nerve of that guy!

00:31:12.892 --> 00:31:16.229
He kept pushing me about whether my salary
started with a three or a four.

00:31:16.312 --> 00:31:17.188
Wow.

00:31:17.271 --> 00:31:20.066
How the hell is that any of his business?

00:31:20.149 --> 00:31:22.193
Do you know what he texted me
the next day?

00:31:22.860 --> 00:31:26.239
"I was deeply moved by your story
of trying to find your true self."

00:31:26.322 --> 00:31:28.366
"I hope you find the right person."

00:31:28.449 --> 00:31:29.659
Wow.

00:31:29.742 --> 00:31:33.037
It was like an HR text to a candidate
who failed a job interview.

00:31:33.121 --> 00:31:36.082
And I never signed up for an interview!
Are you kidding me?

00:31:36.165 --> 00:31:39.460
Jeez, then just stop
going on those blind dates.

00:31:39.544 --> 00:31:41.045
All they do is make you mad.

00:31:41.129 --> 00:31:44.924
You also saw for yourself last time.
There are no decent men left out there.

00:31:45.967 --> 00:31:49.887
You and I are the birds
that overslept way too much.

00:31:49.971 --> 00:31:55.143
We have to start foraging for crumbs
that the early birds left behind.

00:31:55.226 --> 00:31:57.979
Do we really have to stoop
to looking for crumbs?

00:31:59.605 --> 00:32:00.440
Hey.

00:32:01.190 --> 00:32:03.693
Are you trying to say
that I'm obsessed with men?

00:32:03.776 --> 00:32:06.154
Hey, that's not what I meant.

00:32:06.237 --> 00:32:07.655
Then what did you mean?

00:32:07.739 --> 00:32:10.908
"Can you not live without men?
I'm sick of all your men talk."

00:32:10.992 --> 00:32:12.035
That's it, no?

00:32:12.118 --> 00:32:14.871
Hey, it's only because
that's all you've been talking about.

00:32:14.954 --> 00:32:18.666
And you've never talked to me about men?
What about that guy from your office?

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:22.253
Seriously? He's just one of my colleagues.

00:32:22.336 --> 00:32:25.715
You've been talking about him
an awful lot these last few months.

00:32:26.299 --> 00:32:27.675
What? I have not!

00:32:27.759 --> 00:32:29.969
I mean, definitely not that much.

00:32:32.513 --> 00:32:36.267
I was gonna wait until you told me first,
but I can't do this anymore.

00:32:36.350 --> 00:32:37.351
You like him, don't you?

00:32:38.895 --> 00:32:41.397
Hey, are you insane? No, I don't!

00:32:47.195 --> 00:32:48.613
It's the other way around.

00:32:48.696 --> 00:32:51.032
The other way around? What does that mean?

00:32:51.949 --> 00:32:53.034
Well,

00:32:53.868 --> 00:32:56.037
he asked me out.

00:32:57.622 --> 00:32:58.456
Hey!

00:33:01.167 --> 00:33:03.753
Why are you dropping this bomb on me now?

00:33:03.836 --> 00:33:04.962
When was this?

00:33:05.046 --> 00:33:08.174
It's been a while,
and I already turned him down.

00:33:10.384 --> 00:33:11.719
That can't be!

00:33:12.678 --> 00:33:14.305
Why do you keep saying that?

00:33:14.972 --> 00:33:16.808
Something's not right.

00:33:17.892 --> 00:33:19.477
Show me a picture of that guy.

00:33:19.560 --> 00:33:23.231
I don't have one. He's not on Instagram.
He doesn't even have a profile picture.

00:33:24.232 --> 00:33:27.652
Can I please borrow your phone?
I really need to keep filming.

00:33:31.989 --> 00:33:32.824
Let's see.

00:33:34.951 --> 00:33:35.910
-Give it.
-Here.

00:33:41.207 --> 00:33:42.250
What the heck?

00:33:43.042 --> 00:33:43.876
What?

00:33:45.837 --> 00:33:48.631
-He's definitely not your type.
-What?

00:33:48.714 --> 00:33:52.218
He is good-looking,
but not Seo Mi-rae's type.

00:33:52.802 --> 00:33:56.556
You're into guys who are laid-back.
This guy looks too uptight.

00:33:57.557 --> 00:33:58.391
Really?

00:33:59.809 --> 00:34:00.643
Right?

00:34:01.310 --> 00:34:03.896
Yeah, that's what I'm talking about.

00:34:04.480 --> 00:34:05.565
Cheers!

00:34:06.566 --> 00:34:07.400
Cheers.

00:34:12.321 --> 00:34:13.406
I knew it.

00:34:14.407 --> 00:34:15.616
He's not the one.

00:34:49.775 --> 00:34:50.610
You're here.

00:34:51.527 --> 00:34:52.486
Yes.

00:34:56.157 --> 00:34:56.991
Well…

00:34:58.910 --> 00:34:59.744
Your hair.

00:35:03.164 --> 00:35:06.167
It must've gotten there
while I was picking this up for Ms. Yun.

00:35:07.710 --> 00:35:09.128
Congratulations in advance.

00:35:09.629 --> 00:35:13.424
She might not get it,
but I got this just in case she does.

00:35:13.507 --> 00:35:17.220
I hope there's good news for Hwany too.

00:35:18.846 --> 00:35:19.931
I hope so too.

00:35:24.977 --> 00:35:25.811
Oh…

00:35:26.562 --> 00:35:27.396
Ms. Seo?

00:35:28.272 --> 00:35:30.274
About what I said last time…

00:35:31.234 --> 00:35:32.652
Don't worry about it too much.

00:35:36.572 --> 00:35:37.657
I'm fine.

00:35:42.495 --> 00:35:43.579
Let's head in.

00:35:48.167 --> 00:35:53.089
We will now begin the awards ceremony
for the 27th Busan Comics Festival!

00:35:59.804 --> 00:36:03.516
There is no greater honor
than earning the fans' love.

00:36:03.599 --> 00:36:06.477
In that sense,
this is a very meaningful award.

00:36:06.560 --> 00:36:11.482
With an overwhelming number of fan votes,
the Popularity Award goes to…

00:36:12.483 --> 00:36:13.359
Congratulations.

00:36:13.442 --> 00:36:16.988
Yun Song, author of The Man to Know.
Congratulations!

00:36:20.533 --> 00:36:22.243
-Congratulations!
-Thank you.

00:36:22.326 --> 00:36:24.745
…a romance between a chaebol heir
and a hotelier.

00:36:24.829 --> 00:36:27.331
With its charming characters
and an engaging plot,

00:36:27.415 --> 00:36:28.916
it has received a lot of love…

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:30.167
Congratulations.

00:36:30.251 --> 00:36:31.252
Congratulations!

00:36:31.752 --> 00:36:35.256
POPULARITY AWARD
YUN SONG, THE MAN TO KNOW

00:36:35.339 --> 00:36:36.173
All right.

00:36:36.257 --> 00:36:38.759
For a while now,

00:36:38.843 --> 00:36:41.971
the Popularity Award
is all you've been giving me.

00:36:44.640 --> 00:36:48.811
I guess I should be thanking you
for giving me anything at all, right?

00:36:50.688 --> 00:36:53.482
But if you give me this award again
next year,

00:36:54.066 --> 00:36:56.068
I'm seriously going to stop coming.

00:37:03.409 --> 00:37:05.828
I'm just kidding. Oh my God!

00:37:06.454 --> 00:37:07.538
Okay.

00:37:07.621 --> 00:37:08.456
Thank you.

00:37:14.337 --> 00:37:18.758
Next, for bringing a breath of fresh air
into the comics industry,

00:37:18.841 --> 00:37:20.760
the New Artist Award goes to…

00:37:21.260 --> 00:37:23.095
Congratulations, Hwasubun.

00:37:23.804 --> 00:37:24.972
Congratulations.

00:37:26.682 --> 00:37:30.728
Not Okay, a story about student athletes
who fall into a dungeon in another world,

00:37:30.811 --> 00:37:34.065
was praised for its cheeky perspective
and bold expressiveness.

00:37:34.148 --> 00:37:35.691
Congratulations!

00:37:39.945 --> 00:37:41.155
Moving on.

00:37:41.238 --> 00:37:44.116
-It's okay.
-This one's for Webtoon of the Year.

00:37:44.200 --> 00:37:47.370
Only one will rise above the competition
to claim this honor.

00:37:47.453 --> 00:37:48.788
Which one will it be?

00:37:49.372 --> 00:37:52.041
I will now announce the winner
of Webtoon of the Year.

00:37:52.124 --> 00:37:56.629
The winner of Webtoon of the Year
at the 27th Busan Comics Festival is…

00:37:58.964 --> 00:38:02.051
Hwany's PlanC. Congratulations!

00:38:05.054 --> 00:38:05.971
Congratulations!

00:38:06.931 --> 00:38:07.765
It's really me?

00:38:08.391 --> 00:38:11.018
PlanC is a black comedy about young people

00:38:11.102 --> 00:38:14.814
chasing a new life in the countryside,
drawn into a mysterious incident.

00:38:14.897 --> 00:38:18.984
With its solid direction, clear theme,
and high-quality plot,

00:38:19.068 --> 00:38:21.487
it has captivated
readers and critics alike.

00:38:21.570 --> 00:38:22.405
Congratulations.

00:38:22.488 --> 00:38:25.032
Congratulations on your award!

00:38:26.617 --> 00:38:27.618
Thank you.

00:38:30.162 --> 00:38:34.667
I had no idea I'd be presented
such a big award, so--

00:38:34.750 --> 00:38:36.043
You're so handsome!

00:38:36.127 --> 00:38:36.961
Thank you.

00:38:37.044 --> 00:38:38.796
You call that handsome?

00:38:38.879 --> 00:38:40.714
I don't know what to say.

00:38:40.798 --> 00:38:42.049
Don't cry!

00:38:42.133 --> 00:38:44.969
Kyeong-nam, who has helped me a lot
since the very start,

00:38:45.052 --> 00:38:46.971
Director Hwang Byeong-hak,

00:38:47.054 --> 00:38:49.723
Producer Cho Min-seok,
who was my editor for a long time,

00:38:49.807 --> 00:38:50.933
and everyone else who…

00:38:51.016 --> 00:38:52.560
I'm seriously ticked off.

00:38:52.643 --> 00:38:53.853
…I am grateful.

00:38:53.936 --> 00:38:56.188
I'd like to share this award
with all of you.

00:38:56.272 --> 00:38:57.189
Thank you!

00:38:57.273 --> 00:38:58.858
You deserve it!

00:39:04.572 --> 00:39:05.656
Let me go!

00:39:05.739 --> 00:39:08.117
You came all this way,
and this is how you act?

00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:09.702
Hey, I said no!

00:39:10.286 --> 00:39:11.579
Seriously.

00:39:11.662 --> 00:39:12.496
Hey.

00:39:12.580 --> 00:39:15.040
I didn't come all the way here
to be used as a prop.

00:39:15.124 --> 00:39:17.001
Thank you! Yes.

00:39:18.752 --> 00:39:20.421
How could you put it that way?

00:39:20.504 --> 00:39:24.341
He works on the same platform as you.
Why can't you just congratulate him?

00:39:25.092 --> 00:39:27.761
When are you ever going to grow up?

00:39:29.597 --> 00:39:31.265
Last time, you asked me

00:39:31.348 --> 00:39:34.685
if I was going to let a kid claw his way
onto the same day as me.

00:39:36.395 --> 00:39:37.771
Come on, let's just go inside.

00:39:37.855 --> 00:39:39.023
-Let go.
-Please!

00:39:39.106 --> 00:39:40.774
Let go of me. I mean it!

00:39:41.442 --> 00:39:42.276
Seo Mi-rae!

00:40:05.716 --> 00:40:06.634
Are you okay?

00:40:09.261 --> 00:40:11.055
Yes. I'm okay.

00:40:12.723 --> 00:40:13.557
Ms. Yun.

00:40:14.433 --> 00:40:16.352
Why are you out here? Let's go inside.

00:40:17.770 --> 00:40:20.481
This is so annoying, seriously.

00:40:31.200 --> 00:40:33.369
It's all thanks to you guys. Thank you!

00:40:36.455 --> 00:40:39.375
-The drink hits different tonight.
-Congratulations!

00:40:39.458 --> 00:40:41.210
What? Thank you, guys!

00:40:42.294 --> 00:40:44.088
Flowers, really? You keep it.

00:40:47.591 --> 00:40:48.759
Let's take a picture.

00:40:48.842 --> 00:40:49.843
-Sure!
-Sounds good.

00:40:49.927 --> 00:40:52.263
Okay. One, two…

00:40:53.305 --> 00:40:55.558
-Cheers!
-Congratulations.

00:40:56.100 --> 00:40:57.643
Congratulations!

00:41:04.483 --> 00:41:06.485
Hey, you said
you couldn't eat uncooked food.

00:41:09.613 --> 00:41:10.948
I'm gonna start trying it today.

00:41:11.615 --> 00:41:12.449
Yeah?

00:41:13.200 --> 00:41:14.034
Ms. Yun.

00:41:14.118 --> 00:41:17.037
I would love to treat you today.
Let's grab some whiskey.

00:41:17.121 --> 00:41:18.872
-Wow!
-You're the man!

00:41:19.790 --> 00:41:21.292
Something super expensive?

00:41:21.375 --> 00:41:22.293
Of course!

00:41:22.376 --> 00:41:23.294
All right!

00:41:25.087 --> 00:41:26.672
I need to take this.

00:41:28.799 --> 00:41:29.633
Hello?

00:41:30.217 --> 00:41:33.387
What is this? How did you know to call me?

00:41:33.470 --> 00:41:35.556
We're having an after-party right now.

00:41:35.639 --> 00:41:38.225
Wow, thank you. I appreciate it.

00:41:38.309 --> 00:41:40.144
Let's grab a meal when I'm in Seoul.

00:41:40.227 --> 00:41:42.021
Yes, Mr. Cho. Have a good night!

00:41:42.980 --> 00:41:43.814
Mr. Cho?

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:46.233
Producer Cho called you?

00:41:46.775 --> 00:41:47.651
Give me your phone.

00:41:47.735 --> 00:41:49.695
Why? What's this about?

00:41:49.778 --> 00:41:51.488
Damn it, seriously.

00:41:52.489 --> 00:41:54.116
I can't believe this.

00:41:55.200 --> 00:41:56.619
The person you have dialed is…

00:41:56.702 --> 00:41:59.538
Why is it that every time I call him,
it doesn't go through?

00:42:00.706 --> 00:42:01.957
He must be busy right now.

00:42:02.958 --> 00:42:04.627
Ms. Yun, calm down for a second.

00:42:04.710 --> 00:42:05.628
Hey.

00:42:05.711 --> 00:42:08.464
Why does that bastard call you
and act all nice to you

00:42:08.547 --> 00:42:10.549
but leave my calls unanswered for months?

00:42:10.633 --> 00:42:12.134
How on earth would I know that?

00:42:12.217 --> 00:42:14.345
Why did he block me
but stay in touch with you?

00:42:14.428 --> 00:42:16.680
Maybe you were a fucking pain in the ass!

00:42:20.184 --> 00:42:21.018
What?

00:42:21.101 --> 00:42:23.187
That's not what I…

00:42:23.270 --> 00:42:25.439
-Ms. Yun.
-Get a load of this guy.

00:42:25.522 --> 00:42:27.858
I've had enough of your shit.

00:42:27.941 --> 00:42:31.945
Hey, you're scheming with Cho
to get back at me, aren't you?

00:42:32.821 --> 00:42:35.324
I heard he went to Director Hwang
and made a fuss

00:42:35.407 --> 00:42:37.701
about how he was treating us differently.

00:42:37.785 --> 00:42:41.205
Did you ask to have your upload day moved
so you can screw me over?

00:42:41.288 --> 00:42:43.374
That's got nothing to do with this!

00:42:43.457 --> 00:42:45.250
That's not true, Ms. Yun.

00:42:45.334 --> 00:42:47.836
Mr. Hwang decides
matters regarding releases, after all.

00:42:49.546 --> 00:42:52.049
This is hilarious. Hey, then did you…

00:42:54.134 --> 00:42:55.552
No, wait.

00:42:55.636 --> 00:42:58.972
I honestly wasn't going to bring this up.

00:42:59.723 --> 00:43:00.557
What?

00:43:01.975 --> 00:43:03.268
Are you not over me yet?

00:43:08.816 --> 00:43:09.858
What?

00:43:11.193 --> 00:43:14.530
When Cho got us a studio in Hapjeong-dong,

00:43:14.613 --> 00:43:17.991
you were the one who secretly left snacks
in front of my room.

00:43:18.075 --> 00:43:21.704
I saw you run away to the basement
after leaving them several times.

00:43:22.663 --> 00:43:24.665
Hold it right there. That was…

00:43:24.748 --> 00:43:27.334
Hey, you just got rejected, that's all.

00:43:27.418 --> 00:43:30.421
Did you really have to hold a grudge
and screw me over?

00:43:31.046 --> 00:43:32.464
That's so petty of you.

00:43:33.549 --> 00:43:35.467
-Not true.
-What? Did Cho tell you?

00:43:35.551 --> 00:43:37.970
That I threw it all out
without even trying it?

00:43:38.053 --> 00:43:39.555
Unbelievable.

00:43:40.055 --> 00:43:41.557
Those…

00:43:42.891 --> 00:43:43.851
Those were…

00:43:43.934 --> 00:43:45.144
What?

00:43:46.395 --> 00:43:47.896
Those were meant for So-yeong!

00:43:51.775 --> 00:43:52.776
Who is So-yeong?

00:43:56.280 --> 00:43:57.197
Your assistant?

00:44:01.952 --> 00:44:05.289
Ms. Yun? We get it for now.

00:44:06.039 --> 00:44:07.249
It's spilling over.

00:44:09.543 --> 00:44:11.462
Hang on. I need to go to the bathroom.

00:44:12.254 --> 00:44:13.213
Let her through.

00:44:17.760 --> 00:44:18.844
What just happened?

00:44:22.264 --> 00:44:25.768
You know, I'm not the type
to make things up in my head.

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:30.481
Given the situation back then,
this misunderstanding was inevitable.

00:44:30.564 --> 00:44:33.233
I'll bet anyone would have thought
the same.

00:44:33.317 --> 00:44:35.319
-Totally.
-Of course.

00:44:37.738 --> 00:44:40.365
I'm really not like that. Okay?

00:44:41.366 --> 00:44:42.659
I have a boyfriend.

00:44:42.743 --> 00:44:44.578
I have a boyfriend!

00:44:44.661 --> 00:44:45.913
-Okay.
-She has a boyfriend.

00:44:45.996 --> 00:44:47.331
This is ridiculous.

00:44:48.457 --> 00:44:50.542
-We didn't know that.
-What do we do?

00:44:50.626 --> 00:44:52.294
Good God…

00:44:59.384 --> 00:45:01.345
Just a little more. Just over there.

00:45:02.387 --> 00:45:03.597
Oh God!

00:45:10.854 --> 00:45:12.523
God, you're killing me.

00:45:22.032 --> 00:45:22.950
JJONG

00:45:26.829 --> 00:45:29.081
Yes. I'm answering for Ms. Yun.

00:45:29.164 --> 00:45:31.959
Did something happen to Song?

00:45:33.252 --> 00:45:36.171
She received an award
and got drunk at the after-party.

00:45:36.255 --> 00:45:38.006
But she's somewhere safe now?

00:45:38.090 --> 00:45:41.093
Yes. She's back in her room, sleeping.

00:45:41.176 --> 00:45:44.096
So you brought her back. Thank you.

00:45:44.179 --> 00:45:47.850
Sure. But who am I speaking to?

00:45:47.933 --> 00:45:49.601
Oh, I didn't even introduce myself.

00:45:49.685 --> 00:45:52.437
I'm Song's boyfriend.

00:45:53.605 --> 00:45:54.815
What?

00:45:54.898 --> 00:45:57.276
I'm the person who's dating Song.

00:45:57.359 --> 00:45:58.193
Oh my.

00:45:59.862 --> 00:46:02.406
I'm sorry.
I didn't think you'd be her boyfriend.

00:46:02.489 --> 00:46:05.284
It's been a while,
but I guess she hasn't told anyone yet.

00:46:05.367 --> 00:46:08.203
Anyway, thank you for today.

00:46:08.745 --> 00:46:10.956
No problem. Good night.

00:46:22.551 --> 00:46:25.470
So she was telling the truth
about having a boyfriend?

00:46:28.056 --> 00:46:30.559
Did you put her to bed?
You are coming back, right?

00:46:30.642 --> 00:46:32.477
We're going for round two!

00:46:32.978 --> 00:46:34.104
I'm coming over now.

00:46:37.524 --> 00:46:38.859
Mr. Park.

00:46:38.942 --> 00:46:42.112
How long have you been close with Hwany?

00:46:43.739 --> 00:46:45.908
-Who says we're close?
-What?

00:46:46.867 --> 00:46:47.701
You're so funny!

00:46:49.286 --> 00:46:51.538
We are close.
This guy can't live without me.

00:46:51.622 --> 00:46:53.290
I wouldn't say that.

00:47:16.980 --> 00:47:17.814
JI-YEON

00:47:17.898 --> 00:47:21.735
Business trip's boring, huh?
Want to hear how my blind date went?

00:47:23.111 --> 00:47:24.696
She just won't stop.

00:47:27.574 --> 00:47:29.284
Nope.

00:47:43.131 --> 00:47:46.259
Hey, I'll give you ten seconds.
Out with it.

00:47:47.636 --> 00:47:49.304
Come on. Ten seconds is too short.

00:47:51.556 --> 00:47:52.391
What?

00:47:53.183 --> 00:47:54.226
How did…

00:47:54.309 --> 00:47:57.396
I got your car fixed,
so I wanted to take you for a drive.

00:47:57.896 --> 00:47:58.897
Where are you?

00:48:00.565 --> 00:48:02.401
I can't go right now.

00:48:02.484 --> 00:48:03.318
Why is that?

00:48:04.903 --> 00:48:07.739
I hear waves.
I'm also at the beach right now.

00:48:07.823 --> 00:48:09.491
I'll head over to you, then.

00:48:10.659 --> 00:48:12.828
And how are you gonna do that?

00:48:13.328 --> 00:48:15.163
Why do you think I can't?

00:48:18.834 --> 00:48:20.669
How would he come here?

00:48:21.837 --> 00:48:23.255
Who does he think he's kidding?

00:49:13.513 --> 00:49:14.973
You actually made it?

00:49:27.819 --> 00:49:29.029
So warm.

00:49:44.211 --> 00:49:45.504
What are you doing here?

00:49:49.758 --> 00:49:50.592
Hello?

00:49:51.802 --> 00:49:52.886
Hello?

00:50:14.741 --> 00:50:16.535
Oh God! That hurts.

00:50:16.618 --> 00:50:21.581
My mom wanted me to become a doctor
ever since I was little.

00:50:21.665 --> 00:50:24.000
I somehow managed to get through division,

00:50:24.084 --> 00:50:25.836
but I got stuck at fractions.

00:50:25.919 --> 00:50:28.088
This is going to sting. There.

00:50:28.171 --> 00:50:30.841
Goodness, it's okay. It's only a dream.

00:50:31.842 --> 00:50:32.926
Hey, you!

00:50:38.306 --> 00:50:40.433
Who is this hottie?

00:50:40.517 --> 00:50:41.726
Nice.

00:50:41.810 --> 00:50:43.645
Get a grip, will you?

00:50:43.728 --> 00:50:45.564
This is such a weird dream.

00:50:46.565 --> 00:50:48.483
-What?
-This has to be a dream.

00:50:48.567 --> 00:50:50.235
-Isn't this a dream?
-What now?

00:50:53.446 --> 00:50:55.031
-It actually hurts.
-Move.

00:51:14.509 --> 00:51:15.760
Who the heck is this?

00:51:16.761 --> 00:51:19.681
Hand over the paper in the drawer,
and I'll spare your life.

00:51:20.891 --> 00:51:23.602
Yeah. I get what's going on here.

00:51:24.186 --> 00:51:25.854
I'm glad you catch on quickly.

00:51:34.070 --> 00:51:36.740
That's strange.
Someone should be here to save me by now.

00:51:36.823 --> 00:51:38.241
-Wait. Unhand me!
-Hello?

00:51:38.325 --> 00:51:39.743
Is my boyfriend out there?

00:51:46.541 --> 00:51:47.876
My lady!

00:51:47.959 --> 00:51:48.960
My lady!

00:51:49.628 --> 00:51:50.879
You scoundrel!

00:51:53.381 --> 00:51:54.216
Dolsoe?

00:51:54.841 --> 00:51:56.927
My lady! You bastard!

00:51:57.427 --> 00:51:58.970
-Dolsoe!
-What the…

00:51:59.554 --> 00:52:00.639
Yes!

00:53:09.833 --> 00:53:14.838
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon